p: The GC-MS assay revealed for this essential oil obtained at industrial scale two components in high amounts: α-pinene—33.14% and eucalyptol—55.09%. Other compounds found in amounts of more than 1% were: β-fenchyl alcohol (3.20%), α-terpinenyl acetate (1.93%), linalool (1.79%) and 3(10)-caren-4-ol, and acetoacetic acid ester (1.08%). The remaining identified components amount was only 3.77%.
